<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="typical-adj">typical <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'tɪpɪkl/    美 /'tɪpɪkl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>典型的；有代表性的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a typical Italian cafe 
典型的意大利餐馆</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The painting, named Poppy, is a <strong>typical example</strong> of Chen’s style. 
这幅名为“罂粟”的画是陈(逸飞)艺术风格的代表作。</p><footer>北师大② – 3</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>it is typical of sb to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is typical of him to be so gentle. 
他一向都是这么温和。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is typical of John to think about helping others in this way. 
只有约翰才会想到以这种方式去帮助别人。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>typically /'tɪpɪkli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Jack is late again.  <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (是他的特点) to keep others waiting.   （2008 江西改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. It is typical of him  </p></div>